dcterms:description: DublinBikes is a bike-sharing scheme in operation in Dublin City, Ireland. The dataset includes real-time data accessible via an API and historic data recorded every five minutes, which contains timestamps, station states, number of available bikes, and station locations.
dcterms:title: Dublinbike

dcterms:description: This dataset includes the NYC Citi daily bike orders of people using the bike sharing scheme. It contains transaction records from April 1st, 2016 to June 30th, 2016, including bike pickup station, bike drop-off station, bike pick-up time, bike drop-off time, and trip duration.
dcterms:title: NYC-Bikes

dcterms:description: This dataset provides weather conditions at different locations at different historical time points, including temperature, humidity, and wind speed. This weather dataset has been integrated for experiments that use the Dublinbikes dataset.
dcterms:title: Visualcrossing Weather Data
